itemDescription: British Army general and Governor of Western Australia

wikipedia_page.main: Major General Sir Douglas Anthony Kendrew,  (22 July 1910 – 28 February 1989), often known as Joe Kendrew especially during his rugby career, was an officer of the British Army who served in Second World War and the Korean War, an international rugby player, and the 22nd Governor of Western Australia from 1963 to 1974.
